The rescue operation of a deadly explosion in the commercial district of Dhaka, the capital of Bangladesh, concluded on Thursday noon as the death toll stood at 21, local media reported. On Tuesday, around 4:50 p.m., a huge explosion ripped through a building in a major wholesale hub in Dhaka. Assistant Director of Fire Service Aktaruzzaman said the death toll may rise further as 30 more critically-injured patients are undergoing treatment at different hospitals. The cause behind the huge blast is still not known, but officials suspect that accumulated gas might be a likely cause. Detective Branch of Bangladesh Police Thursday detained three people, including the two owners of the five-floor building, Additional Deputy Commissioner (Media) of Dhaka Metropolitan Police KN Roy Niyoti told journalists. "We're inquiring to know whose negligence caused this incident," he said. (With input from Xinhua)